<ul><ul><ul><ul><ul><img src="http://www.geocities.com/starlord51180/randomart.jpg" heigth=150 width=200></ul></ul></ul></ul></ul></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ufalretheverdieing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falreth Everdieing</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.aol.com/dawindow/jc.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/30/00 9:52:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/Tokyo/Dojo/8350/nsjubei4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mana Use</span><hr size=1> Well my SK is allways either oom or fm never seem to end a fight with him in the middle allways empty or full.  But i am only 15th level so dont have to many spells to cast darkness, disease, siphon str and tap thats about it i always siphon the mobs just to keep my str up (cant wait till level 30 when my sword will proc) then i usually tap just to piss it off cuz its fun to smile at them dont really do enough to make it worth it but i enjoy it.  As a palli i am almost allways fm wether i am soloing or grouped but thats cuz i have almost all my buffs cast by my armor so i am just a right clicking fool. <p><a href="http://the.animearchive.org/"><img src="http://www.yale.edu/anime/images/bastard/Bastard-v06.jpg" border="0"><br>Falreth Everdieing<br>47th Paladin of Marr<br>Brell serilis server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/unikayazress.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nikaya Z Ress</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/8/00 11:07:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   mana</span><hr size=1> I'm ususaly close to full mana because I rarely ever have to snare.  I use syphon Str and Shadow vortex on Mezed or STed MObs to help with taunt.  other then that I use invis to get around, FD to stop from dieing, use life tap when i'm bored, and if in Lguk I might use Expulse undead to stop runners with low life.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Nikaya Z'Ress<br>
(I AM A MALE)<br>
lvl 48 Shadow Knight <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uwayun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wayun</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_whitespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/9/00 12:41:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mana</span><hr size=1> Hmmm,<br>
<br>
  I'm usually running about 1-2 bubbles in a fight, but I consistantly team with a Ranger and Mage, so I don't Nuke, I cast my DoT's and keep Fiegn up so I can pull the bad guys away from the party if things get hairy....<br>
<br>
  Other than that, a few pre-fight buffs (Vampiric Embrace, Shield, and the appropriate protection should I need it) and I am ready for action. <br>
<br>
  In combat, typical debuffs (Shadow Vortex, Siphon Strength, Heat Blood, perhaps a Cancel Magic, and Engulfing Darkness) to head the mob into corpsedom.. <br>
<br>
  Typically, that leaves me down by 20% (one bubble) a bit more if they resist, or the debuff needs to be reapplyed, or I need to recast the pet.. Other than that... *shrug* <p>Wayun Starchaser
Warrior of the 28th Season
<BR>
Valeer Shadowsbaine
Shadow Knight of the 40th Season</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udyninvifargent.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dynin Vifargent</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/11/00 12:25:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mana</span><hr size=1> to show how much mana i use it's really simple...<br>
