but i dot, lifetap, buff....<br>
i'm sitting my ass off more than most casters i know... /sigh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uwarith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/11/00 8:52:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mana</span><hr size=1> Not being an SK or have an SK alt I probly should not post here but what the hey.<br>
<br>
With Clarity I med about every 4th or 5th mob.<br>
<br>
No Clarity I dont bother with medding or that is all That I would be doing.  Ie I med just enough in between mobs for a Yaulp and a stun or two if I am lucky.<br>
<br>
 <p>Warith the Paladin<br>
42 Paladin of Rodcet Nife<br>
Brell </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ufenubsy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenubsy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(8/27/00 3:17:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mana Use</span><hr size=1> I will try and go through my normal casting growing up using each spell lvl as the next point.  I will start with lvl 30 because before lvl 30 you dont have a great range of spells available to you.  At lvl 30 if I was pulling I would always pull with disease cloud it has the intial 5 damage and also does 1 damage per round so basically keeps the mob from healing every tick so ends up doing alot more for your 10 mana.  I kept Vampiric up but not always depended really it really doesnt start kicking major butt till later on and having a low dex it would rarly go off for me on a slow 2h weapon.  I would siphon str on the majority of the mobs if I didnt pull with disease I did with this.  Now if I was in a group that was mowing down low blues then I would not cast heat blood because it takes somewere between 60 and 90 sec to do its full damage.  Its very mana effecient though for damage. I would always try and stay at about 80% if pulling if I got in trouble I would tap till oom.  If killing mobs slower or I was not pulling then I would drop heat blood because I had the time to med and tap as I could.  I only snared when there was no snarer around since it takes just as long as heat blood and heat blood does more damage.  <br>
    At lvl 39 u get some nice new additions to your spellbook.  I did the same at lvl 39 as I did at 30 but I finally stopped using disease cloud in there someplace.  I went to pulling with Shadow Vortex for the 12 ac and siphon for the str.  I then became very fond of Heart Flutter.  It does not do as much damage as heat blood but it is faster and debuffs a mobs AC and ATK as well which really pisses them off at you and allows u to tank better.  By this point I always had vampiric up because it was doing 20 damage by now and well worth it to me even though I still process'ed a small amount.<br>
    At lvl 49 u get some killer spells u get Dooming Darkness which is a 300 point Dot that eats the mana bar so be prepared.  It also overrides snare as long as the snarer is not higher so be careful your dot does not wear off towards the end of the fight leaving a mob unsnared.  I only use this if I have clarity or am not pulling because of the mana drain.  If I am primary snarer and have to pull and do not have clarity I do not think to use dooming because my first job is a puller not a caster I use a lower lvl snare to keep my mana up.  <br>
   In general when I am pulling I do not think about casting as much because my primary concern is pulling.  I will never forget the first time I heard a puller say he was oom and needed to med when the casters were ready to go.  That personally got me extremely pissed off.  When I am a back up tank I unload everything I have I do not tap unless I am down health because it is ver ineffecient.  I use a 2h blunt weapon with a delay of 36 so always try and cast right after I swing.  Always if a target is mez'ed I will Siphon STR and Shadow vortex while taunting then as a last bit to piss it off if I have the mana drop Heart Flutter to break the mez.  Just remember you are first and formost a tank but you can not stand toe to toe with non-hybrids without your spells.  With your spells you can be a a real beast of a tank.  Learn the balance that works best for you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nurbok<br>
Shadowknight 50<br>
Crimson Rage<br>
